headline.main: 30 ITALIAN PLANES BAGGED IN ALBANIA; R. A. F. Fliers Report Downing 26 and Damaging 9 Others in One Great Dogfight 30 ITALIAN PLANES BAGGED IN ALBANIA

lead_paragraph: ATHENS, Feb. 28 -- A formation of British Hurricane and Gladiator fighter planes on patrol over the southern sector of the Albanian front today met a greatly superior formation of Italian aircraft, and in the combat that ensued shot down twenty-six of the Italian planes, it was officially announced by the British tonight.
abstract: Brit rept 26 Ital planes downed, 9 damaged, Albanian southern sector; Brit planes and Greek forces attack Kodra village; Brit describe previous day's air battle before attack on Valona airdrome; Greeks down 2 Ital planes; bad weather restricts land fighting; Itals rept 2 enemy planes downed, Albanian front
